    • Uses of ISyntacticStructure in grammarModel.structure

      Subinterfaces of ISyntacticStructure in grammarModel.structure 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  ISyntacticBranch
      ISyntacticBranch is a syntactic structure that represents the derivation of a non-terminal node in a syntactic tree.
      interface  ISyntacticGrove
      ISyntacticGrove is a container of syntax trees, i.e. syntax branches whose name is the start element of the context-free grammar at use.
      interface  ISyntacticLeaf
      ISyntacticLeaf is a terminal syntactic structure, representing the terminal node of a syntax tree.
